description.narrative: Through UNICEF support, provincial, district and health facility human resource and institutional capacity to deliver an integrated nutrition program improved in 98% of the health facilities, leading to treatment of 19,802 (11,003 girls; 9,096 boys) were treated for severe acute malnutrition across the country with severe acute malnutrition including timely response to nutrition emergency in cyclone affected districts. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
